                        "AcquisitionStrategy": {
                            "val": "To provide improved operational effectiveness, the Army will use the Defense Ordnance Technology Consortium (DOTC) OTA to execute a competitive initial concept definition (CD) with multiple contractors. From the CD phase, rapid prototype development approaches will utilize detailed modeling and simulation of the future interceptor as well as conduct prototype development of high-risk hardware technologies. The prototype technologies and detailed simulation based interceptor design will be used to competitively down select to a single vendor. This approach and the resulting technologies and designs will inform the selection of Acquisition Strategy (traditional or 804 Middle Tier) most advantageous for this project.  This PB21 submission presents R-4 and R-4a schedule information in traditional acquisition terminology that will be updated with 804 Middle Tier terminology if utilized."
                        }
